src/lib/components/CopyButton.react.js.description:
CopyButton is an button that when clicked copies text to the clipboard.
 It has an input value which is the content to be copied.
Additional properties of typical Dash components

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

disabled.description: Indicates wheather the user can interact with the element

children.description: Array that holds components to render

n_clicks.description: Number of times the button has been clicked.

n_clicks_timestamp.description: Last time the button was clicked.

className.description: Often used with CSS to style elements with common properties.

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.
